FBIS4-6652 "dreas077_a_94031" FBIS-EAS-94-077 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan EPA: Still Stagnation in Regional Economies EPA: Still Stagnation in Regional Economies OW1904094494 Tokyo KYODO in English 0857 GMT 19 Apr 94 OW1904094494 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, April 19 KYODO -- The Economic Planning Agency said Tuesday [19 April] regional economies generally remain stagnant although some bright factors are seen in Kyushu and Hokkaido. In Kyushu, southern Japan, industrial production indexes improved consecutively in January and February, compared with the preceding months, the agency said. The agency added, however, sales at large retail stores remained sluggish in major urban regions, including Tokyo, Nagoya and Osaka.
